rComments: Really great at teaching and he explains all the concepts really well! Very nice outside of class as well and quite accessible in terms of office hours. If you have to take MAT136 take it with him if hes teaching!

Jeffrey Pike is a wonderful professor, he is definitely a very clear and professional lecturer and the pace of his lectures is very good. He lets you know what is expected for the different types of questions and his examples are also very helpful. Outside of class, during office hours, he is a very encouraging person, so don't be afraid to ask!

Professor Pike is an amazing teacher, his lectures are very clear and well thought out, he teaches at a very good pace. Examples that he teaches in class are also very helpful and (sometimes) useful for the midterm. If you go to his office hours you'll see that he is a very approachable and nice professor to talk to. I like math after his class.

He is a thorough professor. His teaching is very professional and to the point. Classes are worth going to because they aren't very intense or fast. He always gets his points clearly through to students. Moreover, he seems to be very approachable and nice as a person. Definitely worth taking his class.
